OL,24,ANext Page BCh Is News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,389,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38805
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F388A1779214266
OL,3,CSiam Cup victory for Guernsey men and
OL,4,CJersey women
OL,6,FThe first 3 points of the men's game
OL,7,Fwent to Guernsey from Ciaran McGann's
OL,8,Fpenalty.
OL,10,FJersey's Jack McFarlane converted a
OL,11,Ftry bringing the score to 7-3.
OL,13,FThe greens immediately replied making
OL,14,Fthe score 8-7 with a try from Dale
OL,15,FRutledge.
OL,17,FAnother penalty from Guernsey took the
OL,18,Fscore to 11-7.
OL,20,FA Dom Rice try converted which made it
OL,21,F18-7 to the Sarnian side at half time.
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G5/10
OL,2,W+.!/*%/*%/*%/*%+,"-$ /(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,
